45 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
46 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
47 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
48 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
49 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
50 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
51  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
52 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
53 #else
54 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
55 #endif
56 #endif
57 
58 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
59 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
60 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
61 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
62 #else
63 #error "unknown compiler"
64 #endif
65 
66 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
67 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
68 #else
69 #include <cstdio>
70 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
71  do { \
72  fputs(msg, stderr); \
73  DNNL_TRAP(); \
74  } while (0)
75 #endif

86 
91 struct error : public std::exception {
92  dnnl_status_t status;
93  const char *message;
94 
99  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
100  : status(status), message(message) {}
101 
103  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
104 
110  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
111  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
112  }
113 };
114 
116 template <typename T>
117 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
118  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
119  const int size = (int)v.size();
120  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
121  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
122 }
124 
126 template <typename T>
127 struct handle_traits {};
128 
142 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
143 struct handle {
144 private:
145  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
146  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
147 
148 protected:
149  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
150  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
151 
152 public:
160  handle() = default;
161 
163  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
165  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
167  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
169  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
170 
176  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
177 
183  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
184  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
185  }
186 
192  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
193  T result = data_.get();
194  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
195  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
196  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
197  return result;
198  }
199 
204  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
205 
209  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
210 
217  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
218  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
219  }
220 
227  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
228 };
229

376 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
377  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
378  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
379  // returns a C type.
380  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
381  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
382  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
383  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
384  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
385 }

641 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
642  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
643  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
644  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
645  } \
646 \
647  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
648  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
649  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
650  } \
651 \
652  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
653  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
654  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
655  } \
656 \
657  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
658  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
659  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
660  return lhs; \
661  } \
662 \
663  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
664  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
665  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
666  return lhs; \
667  } \
668 \
669  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
670  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
671  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
672  return lhs; \
673  } \
674 \
675  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
676  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
677  }
678 
679 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
680 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

838 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
839  friend struct primitive;
840  friend struct reorder;
841 
843  enum class kind {
845  any = dnnl_any_engine,
847  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
849  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
850  };
851 
852  using handle::handle;
853 
856  engine() = default;
857 
862  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
863  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
864  }
865 
871  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
872  dnnl_engine_t engine;
873  error::wrap_c_api(
874  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
875  "could not create an engine");
876  reset(engine);
877  }
878 
879 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
880  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
887  dnnl_engine_t engine;
888  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
889  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
890  "could not create an engine");
891  reset(engine);
892  }
893 #endif
894 
899  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
900  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
901  error::wrap_c_api(
902  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
903  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
904  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
905  reset(c_engine, true);
906  }
907 
910  kind get_kind() const {
911  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
912  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
913  "could not get kind of an engine");
914  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
915  }
916 
917 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
918  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
921  cl_context context = nullptr;
922  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
923  "could not get an OpenCL context from an engine");
924  return context;
925  }
926 
929  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
930  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
931  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
932  "could not get an OpenCL device from an engine");
933  return device;
934  }
935 #endif
936 
942  template <typename primitive_desc>
943  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
944  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
945  }
946 
947 private:
948  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
949  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
950  }
951 
952  template <typename primitive_desc>
953  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
954  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
955  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
956  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
957  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
958  return engine(c_engine, true);
959  }
960 };

1041 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1042  using handle::handle;
1043 
1045  enum class flags : unsigned {
1048  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1050  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1052  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1054  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1055  };
1056 
1059  stream() = default;
1060 
1067  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags,
1068  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1069  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1070  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, engine.get(),
1071  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags),
1072  attr.get(true)),
1073  "could not create a stream");
1074  reset(stream);
1075  }
1076 
1077 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1078  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1083  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1084  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1085  "could not create a stream");
1086  reset(stream);
1087  }
1088 
1091  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1092  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1093  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1094  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1095  return queue;
1096  }
1097 #endif
1098 
1101  stream &wait() {
1102  error::wrap_c_api(
1103  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1104  return *this;
1105  }
1106 };

1748 
1750  struct desc {
1751  friend struct memory;
1753  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1754 
1757  desc() : data() {}
1758 
1774  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1775  format_tag format_tag, bool allow_empty = false)
1776  : data() {
1777  validate_dims(dims);
1778  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1779  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1780  convert_to_c(format_tag));
1781  if (!allow_empty)
1782  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1783  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1784  "format tag");
1785  }
1786 
1802  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1803  const memory::dims &strides, bool allow_empty = false)
1804  : data() {
1805  validate_dims(dims);
1806  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)dims.size());
1807  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1808  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1809  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1810  if (!allow_empty)
1811  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1812  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1813  "strides");
1814  }
1815 
1819  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1820 
1823  //
1832  desc submemory_desc(const memory::dims &dims,
1833  const memory::dims &offsets, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1834  validate_dims(dims, data.ndims);
1835  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1836  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1837  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1838  &sub_md, &data, dims.data(), offsets.data());
1839  if (!allow_empty)
1840  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1841  return desc(sub_md);
1842  }
1843 
1888  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1889  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(dims, 1);
1890  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1891  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1892  &out_md, &data, (int)dims.size(), dims.data());
1893  if (!allow_empty)
1894  error::wrap_c_api(
1895  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1896  return desc(out_md);
1897  }
1898 
1935  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1936  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1937  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
1938  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1939  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
1940  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
1941  if (!allow_empty)
1942  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1943  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
1944  return desc(out_md);
1945  }
1946 
1951  memory::dims dims() const {
1952  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
1953  }
1954 
1957  memory::data_type data_type() const {
1958  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
1959  }
1960 
1965  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1966 
1970  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1971 
1976  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1977  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1978  }
1979 
1984  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1985  };
1986 
1991  memory() = default;
1992 
2013  memory(const desc &md, const engine &engine, void *handle) {
2014  dnnl_memory_t result;
2015  error::wrap_c_api(
2016  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, engine.get(), handle),
2017  "could not create a memory object");
2018  reset(result);
2019  }
2020 
2027  memory(const desc &md, const engine &engine)
2028  : memory(md, engine, DNNL_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}
2029 
2031  desc get_desc() const {
2032  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc;
2033  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_memory_desc(get(), &cdesc),
2034  "could not get a memory descriptor from a memory object");
2035  return desc(*cdesc);
2036  }
2037 
2039  engine get_engine() const {
2040  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
2041  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_engine(get(), &c_engine),
2042  "could not get an engine from a memory object");
2043  return engine(c_engine, true);
2044  }

2828  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2829  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
2830  "could not retrieve implementation info string from a "
2831  "primitive descriptor");
2832  return res;
2833  }

2838  memory::dim query_s64(query what) const {
2839  memory::dim res;
2840  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2841  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &res);
2842  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
2843  }
2844 
2859  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2860  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2861  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2862  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2863  query::exec_arg_md};
2864  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2865  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2866  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2867  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2868 
2869  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2870  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2871  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2872  }

2999  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_c_attr;
3000  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_c_attr),
3001  "could not get attributes from a primitive descriptor");
3002  dnnl_primitive_attr_t c_attr;
3003  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&c_attr, const_c_attr),
3004  "could not clone primitive attributes");

3010  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
3011  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
3012  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
3013  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3014  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3015  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);

3018 protected:
3022  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3023  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3024  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3025  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3026  reset(new_pd);
3027  }
3028 
3042  primitive_desc_base(
3043  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3044  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3045 
3057  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3058  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
3059  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
3060 
3074  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3075  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3076  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3077  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3078  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3079 
3080  dnnl_status_t rc;
3081 
3082  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3083  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3084  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3085 
3086  // Check that primitive kind matches
3087  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3088  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3089  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3090  error::wrap_c_api(
3091  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3092  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3093  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3094  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3095 
3096  // Check that propagation kind matches
3097  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3098  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3099  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3100 
3101  // Something went wrong
3102  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3103  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3104  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3105  "descriptor");
3106 
3107  // Everything is fine
3108  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3109  || (rc == dnnl_success
3110  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3111  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3112  reset_with_clone(pd);
3113  return;
3114  }
3115 
3116  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3117  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3118  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3119  }
3120 
3121  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3122 };
3123

3259 
3261 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3262  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3263  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
3264  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
3265  for (const auto &s : mems)
3266  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
3267  return c_mems;
3268 }

3476 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3477  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3478 
3479  primitive_desc() = default;
3480 
3503  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3504  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3505  bool allow_empty = false)
3506  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3507  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3508  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3509  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3510  if (!allow_empty)
3511  error::wrap_c_api(
3512  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3513  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3514  fetch_impl();
3515  }
3516 
3521  bool next_impl() {
3522  dnnl_status_t status
3523  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3524  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3525  error::wrap_c_api(
3526  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3527  fetch_impl();
3528  return true;
3529  }
3530 
3531 private:
3532  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3533  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3534  void fetch_impl() {
3535  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3536  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3537  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3538  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3539  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3540  "descriptor iterator");
3541  reset(pd);
3542  }
3543 };

7584  return base::query_md(query::exec_arg_md, DNNL_ARG_DIFF_DST_ITER_C);
7585  }
7586 
7587 protected:
7588  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7589 
7590  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7591  //
7592  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7593  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7594  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7595  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7596  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7597  //
7598  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7599  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7600  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7601  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7602  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7603  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7604  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7605  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7606  dnnl_status_t rc;
7607  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7608  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7609  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7610  "for an RNN primitive");
7611 
7612  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7613  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7614  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7615 
7616  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7617  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7618  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7619  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7620 
7621  if (!ok)
7622  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7623  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7624  "RNN primitive");
7625 
7626  reset_with_clone(pd);
7627  }
7628 };

7631 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {
7633  struct desc {
7634  dnnl_rnn_desc_t data;
7635 
7692  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm activation, rnn_direction direction,
7693  const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
7694  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,
7695  const memory::desc &weights_layer_desc,
7696  const memory::desc &weights_iter_desc,
7697  const memory::desc &bias_desc,
7698  const memory::desc &dst_layer_desc,
7699  const memory::desc &dst_iter_desc,
7700  rnn_flags flags = rnn_flags::undef, float alpha = 0.0f,
7701  float beta = 0.0f) {
7702  error::wrap_c_api(
7703  dnnl_vanilla_rnn_forward_desc_init(&data,
7704  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
7705  dnnl::convert_to_c(activation),
7706  dnnl::convert_to_c(direction), &src_layer_desc.data,
7707  &src_iter_desc.data, &weights_layer_desc.data,
7708  &weights_iter_desc.data, &bias_desc.data,
7709  &dst_layer_desc.data, &dst_iter_desc.data,
7710  dnnl::convert_to_c(flags), alpha, beta),
7711  "could not create a descriptor for a vanilla RNN forward "
7712  "propagation primitive");
7713  }
7714  };

10303 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
10305  struct desc {
10306  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
10307 
10329  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10330  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10331  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10332  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10333  convert_to_c(algorithm), nullptr,
10334  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10335  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10336  }
10337 
10352  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10353  const std::vector<float> &factors,
10354  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
10355  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10356  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10357  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10358  convert_to_c(algorithm), &factors[0],
10359  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
10360  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10361  }
10362 
10385  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10386  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
10387  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10388  if (!factors.empty())
10389  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10390  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10391  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10392  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10393  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10394  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10395  }
10396  };

10399  struct primitive_desc : public dnnl::primitive_desc {
10401  primitive_desc() = default;
10402 
10413  primitive_desc(const desc &desc, const engine &engine,
10414  bool allow_empty = false)
10415  : dnnl::primitive_desc(
10416  &desc.data, nullptr, engine, nullptr, allow_empty) {}
10417 
10429  primitive_desc(const desc &desc, const primitive_attr &attr,
10430  const engine &engine, bool allow_empty = false)
10431  : dnnl::primitive_desc(
10432  &desc.data, &attr, engine, nullptr, allow_empty) {}
10433 
10440  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
10441  : dnnl::primitive_desc(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::resampling,

10447

10450  };

10453  resampling_forward() = default;
10454 
10458  resampling_forward(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd) {}
10459 };
10460 
10462 struct resampling_backward : public primitive {
10464  struct desc {
10465  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
10466 
10481  desc(algorithm algorithm, const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
10482  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
10483  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
10484  convert_to_c(algorithm), nullptr,
10485  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
10486  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
10487  }
10488 
10504  desc(algorithm algorithm, const std::vector<float> &factors,
10505  const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
10506  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
10507  if (!factors.empty())
10508  memory::validate_dims(factors, diff_src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10509  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
10510  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10511  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
10512  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
10513  }
10514  };

10773 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &stream,
10774  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10775  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10776  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10777  for (const auto &a : args)
10778  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10779 
10780  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
10781  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10782  "could not execute a primitive");
10783 }
